<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Standard Oil/11:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-29T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            29, 1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>30. Department’s No. 27 November 17, 7 p.m. Your No. 44, November 26,
                                11 a.m.<note n="6" xml:id="d406fn6">Not printed.</note></p>
                            <p>The Persian Minister at Washington states that Nicholson of Anglo
                                Persian Company is proceeding to Persia to conclude negotiations for
                                Russian concessions in Northern Persia. Make sure that the new
                                Foreign Minister clearly understands the position of this Government
                                and of American companies as outlined in previous instructions.
                                Report to the Department regarding British influence in Cabinet.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>